cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on learning high-level features from video data, which is a core area of computer vision research. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper proposes a joint visual-linguistic model to learn bidirectional joint distributions over sequences of visual and linguistic tokens, which is a natural fit for the Computation and Language category. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a self-supervised learning approach to leverage the abundance of unlabeled data available on platforms like YouTube, which is a core area of machine learning research. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video data and proposes a model for video captioning, which is a natural fit for the Multimedia category. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a joint model for video and language representation learning, which is a core area of artificial intelligence research.
